hysiology of Fishes, pp. 497-518. , ed. M. A. Ali. New York: Plenum Press; Salvanes, A.G.V., Hart, P.J.B., Is individual variation in competitive performance of reared juvenile cod influenced by haemoglobin genotype? (2000) Sarsia, 85, pp. 265-274; Sehurmann, H., Steffensen, J.F., Lethal oxygen levels at different temperatures and the preferred temperature during hypoxia of the Atlantic cod, Gadus morhua L. (1992) J. Fish Biol., 41, pp. 927-934; Schurmann, H., Steffensen, J.F., Spontaneous swimming activity of Atlantic cod Gadus morhua exposed to graded hypoxia at three temperatures (1994) J. Exp. Biol., 197, pp. 129-142; Schurmann, H., Steffensen, J.F., Lomholt, J.P., The influence of hypoxia on the preferred temperature of rainbow trout Oncorhynchus mykiss (1991) J. Exp. Biol., 157, pp. 75-86; Sick, K., Haemoglobin polymorphism in fishes (1961) Nature, 192, pp. 894-896; Sick, K., Haemoglobin polymorphism of cod in the Baltic and the Danish Belt Sea (1965) Hereditas, 54, pp. 19-48; Sick, K., Haemoglobin polymorphism of cod in the North Sea and the North Atlantic Ocean (1965) Hereditas, 54, pp. 49-69; Stevens, E.D., Sutterlin, A.M., Heat transfer between fish and ambient water (1976) J. Exp. Biol., 65, pp. 131-145","Petersen, M.F.; Marine Biological Laboratory, University of Copenhagen, Strandpromenaden 5, DK-3000 Helsingør, Denmark; email: mfpetersen@zi.ku.dk",,,,,,,,00220949,,JEBIA,12477905,"English","J. Exp. Biol.",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-0037255978
